ğŸ§­ 1ï¸âƒ£ Authentication vs Authorization
Term	Meaning	Example
Authentication	Verifies who you are	Logging in with username/password or token
Authorization	Verifies what you can access	Whether you can access /admin endpoint after login

In short:

ğŸ§â€â™‚ï¸ Authentication = Identity check
ğŸ” Authorization = Access control

âš™ï¸ 2ï¸âƒ£ Authentication Types in RestAssured

RestAssured supports many types of authentication out of the box.

ğŸ”¹ Basic Authentication

Used when API requires username & password.

given()
    .auth()
    .basic("username", "password")
.when()
    .get("https://api.example.com/users")
.then()
    .statusCode(200);


ğŸ§  Sends credentials as Base64 encoded string in the request header:

Authorization: Basic dXNlcm5hbWU6cGFzc3dvcmQ=

ğŸ”¹ Preemptive Basic Auth

Sends credentials immediately (not after 401 challenge).

given()
    .auth()
    .preemptive()
    .basic("username", "password")
.when()
    .get("https://api.example.com/users")
.then()
    .statusCode(200);

ğŸ”¹ Digest Authentication

More secure than basic (hash-based challengeâ€“response).

given()
    .auth()
    .digest("username", "password")
.when()
    .get("https://api.example.com/secure-data")
.then()
    .statusCode(200);

ğŸ”¹ Bearer Token / OAuth2 Token

Most common for modern APIs.

given()
    .auth()
    .oauth2("your_access_token_here")
.when()
    .get("https://api.example.com/user/profile")
.then()
    .statusCode(200);


Or manually set header:

given()
    .header("Authorization", "Bearer " + token)
.when()
    .get("https://api.example.com/data");

ğŸ”¹ API Key

Some APIs use API keys (passed as header or query param).

// Header-based key
given()
    .header("x-api-key", "your_api_key_here")
.when()
    .get("https://api.example.com/data");

// Query param-based key
given()
    .queryParam("api_key", "your_api_key_here")
.when()
    .get("https://api.example.com/data");

ğŸ§© 3ï¸âƒ£ Authorization (Access Control)

Once youâ€™re authenticated, authorization is verified by the API itself.

Example:

given()
    .auth()
    .oauth2(adminToken)
.when()
    .get("/admin/dashboard")
.then()
    .statusCode(200); // authorized

given()
    .auth()
    .oauth2(userToken)
.when()
    .get("/admin/dashboard")
.then()
    .statusCode(403); // forbidden (not authorized)

ğŸ§  Summary
Type	Example Method	Common Use
Basic Auth	.auth().basic("u","p")	Internal or legacy APIs
Digest Auth	.auth().digest("u","p")	Secure internal APIs
OAuth2 / Bearer	.auth().oauth2(token)	Modern secured APIs
API Key	.header("x-api-key", key)	External APIs (like Google, AWS)

Would you like me to show how to get a token dynamically (login â†’ extract token â†’ use in next API) using RestAssured?

